29/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- Outgoing Naval Forces Commander Vice-Admiral Bulent Alpkaya warned on Thursday (28 August) of domestic threats posed by fundamentalist and separatist forces. His remarks came during a ceremony in which he handed over duties to his successor, Vice-Admiral Ozden Ornek. Alpkaya urged that the navy continue fighting what he described as destructive tendencies.
In other news Thursday, the leader of the Orthodox Church, Ecumenical Patriarch Bartholomeos, met with Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan in Ankara, and asked that Turkey reopen a Greek Orthodox seminary closed down more than 30 years ago. He said it would underscore co-operation between the two NATO allies. (Anadolu Agency, ANA, AFP - 28/08/03)
